{
  "texts": [
    "The quantified data on which AI relies act as a moral anesthetic, reducing human problems to technical issues (Heaven 2022).",
    "AI can never be truly \"responsible\" or \"mature.\"",
    "AI can fail due to \"limitations in algorithmic models, poorly scoped system goals, or problems with integration with other systems\" (Renieris et al. 2022).",
    "AI can diminish agency and increase passivity and emotional distance (Friedland 2019).Humans ought to retain control, instead of passively accepting whatever digital technology dispenses (Lindebaum et al. 2020).",
    "We should be wary of the habitual reinforcements of ceding decision-making to AI (Gigerenzer 2022)."
  ]
}